<br>
Using the argument that you kill him with no deaths, and thus should get double slots seems much like Aegirson's old Planar post.  I am sure several guilds on the rotation could kill Sev with half or less of their normal raiding force - should they get two slots?  FK/LoM are a single entity for everything but planes, and (now, attempting) Sev.  I don't think it's fair to the rest of us that it works like this.  Either you are an Alliance or you aren't.<br>
<br>
In other news, NB *finally* had a green scale drop off our 8th or so Hoshkar.  We also had an old member (warrior) return to us after a long break, so still need 2 scales.  We will probably only need 1-2 more Sevs and will be done with this rotation.  When we get those, we will take our name out, so that other guilds can benefit from our slot.<br>
<br>
In closing, I think FK/LoM should either be Allies for all rotations or none. <p><p><a href="http://www.noble-blade.net"><img src="http://www.noble-blade.net/images/ezboard/sig-small.gif" align="left" border="0"></a>Karadin Firethorne<br>Assassin of The Rathe<br><a href="http://www.noble-blade.net">Noble Blade</a> 
